                                                  written lines: 26; Masorah magna occupies generally one to four lines in the lower and one to three lines in the upper margin of the page. A number of masoretic notes is given at the end of each book. All the books except Judges, commence a new page. The beginning and the end of the Hafṭarot are indicated in the margin. An annual cycle for the complete Bible is also noted in various places.
